69// Concrete instance of RecordableEncodedFrame wrapping needed content
70// from EncodedFrame.
71class WebRtcRecordableEncodedFrame : public RecordableEncodedFrame {
72 public:
73 explicit WebRtcRecordableEncodedFrame(const EncodedFrame& frame)
74 : buffer_(frame.GetEncodedData()),
75 render_time_ms_(frame.RenderTime()),
76 codec_(frame.CodecSpecific()->codecType),
77 is_key_frame_(frame.FrameType() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey),
78 resolution_{frame.EncodedImage()._encodedWidth,
79 frame.EncodedImage()._encodedHeight} {
80 if (frame.ColorSpace()) {
81 color_space_ = *frame.ColorSpace();
82 }
83 }
84
85 // VideoEncodedSinkInterface::FrameBuffer
86 rtc::scoped_refptr<const EncodedImageBufferInterface> encoded_buffer()
87 const override {
88 return buffer_;
89 }
90
91 absl::optional<webrtc::ColorSpace> color_space() const override {
92 return color_space_;
93 }
94
95 VideoCodecType codec() const override { return codec_; }
96
97 bool is_key_frame() const override { return is_key_frame_; }
98
99 EncodedResolution resolution() const override { return resolution_; }
100
101 Timestamp render_time() const override {
102 return Timestamp::Millis(render_time_ms_);
103 }
104
105 private:
106 rtc::scoped_refptr<EncodedImageBufferInterface> buffer_;
107 int64_t render_time_ms_;
108 VideoCodecType codec_;
109 bool is_key_frame_;
110 EncodedResolution resolution_;
111 absl::optional<webrtc::ColorSpace> color_space_;
112};
113
114VideoCodec CreateDecoderVideoCodec(const VideoReceiveStream::Decoder& decoder) {
115 VideoCodec codec;
116 codec.codecType = PayloadStringToCodecType(decoder.video_format.name);
117
118 if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP8) {
119 *(codec.VP8()) = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp8Settings();
120 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
121 *(codec.VP9()) = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp9Settings();
122 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecH264) {
123 *(codec.H264()) = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultH264Settings();
124 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecMultiplex) {
125 VideoReceiveStream::Decoder associated_decoder = decoder;
126 associated_decoder.video_format =
127 SdpVideoFormat(CodecTypeToPayloadString(kVideoCodecVP9));
128 VideoCodec associated_codec = CreateDecoderVideoCodec(associated_decoder);
129 associated_codec.codecType = kVideoCodecMultiplex;
130 return associated_codec;
131 }
132
133 codec.width = 320;
134 codec.height = 180;
135 const int kDefaultStartBitrate = 300;
136 codec.startBitrate = codec.minBitrate = codec.maxBitrate =
137 kDefaultStartBitrate;
138
139 return codec;
140}

142// Video decoder class to be used for unknown codecs. Doesn't support decoding
143// but logs messages to LS_ERROR.
144class NullVideoDecoder : public webrtc::VideoDecoder {
145 public:
146 int32_t InitDecode(const webrtc::VideoCodec* codec_settings,
147 int32_t number_of_cores) override {
148 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Can't initialize NullVideoDecoder.";
149 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
150 }
151
152 int32_t Decode(const webrtc::EncodedImage& input_image,
153 bool missing_frames,
154 int64_t render_time_ms) override {
155 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "The NullVideoDecoder doesn't support decoding.";
156 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
157 }
158
159 int32_t RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(
160 webrtc::DecodedImageCallback* callback) override {
161 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
162 << "Can't register decode complete callback on NullVideoDecoder.";
163 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
164 }
165
166 int32_t Release() override { return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK; }
167
168 DecoderInfo GetDecoderInfo() const override {
169 DecoderInfo info;
170 info.implementation_name = "NullVideoDecoder";
171 return info;
172 }
173 const char* ImplementationName() const override { return "NullVideoDecoder"; }
174};

185VideoReceiveStream::VideoReceiveStream(
186 TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
187 RtpStreamReceiverControllerInterface* receiver_controller,
188 int num_cpu_cores,
189 PacketRouter* packet_router,
190 VideoReceiveStream::Config config,
191 ProcessThread* process_thread,
192 CallStats* call_stats,
193 Clock* clock,
194 VCMTiming* timing)
195 : task_queue_factory_(task_queue_factory),
196 transport_adapter_(config.rtcp_send_transport),
197 config_(std::move(config)),
198 num_cpu_cores_(num_cpu_cores),
199 process_thread_(process_thread),
200 clock_(clock),
201 call_stats_(call_stats),
202 source_tracker_(clock_),
203 stats_proxy_(&config_, clock_),
204 rtp_receive_statistics_(ReceiveStatistics::Create(clock_)),
205 timing_(timing),
206 video_receiver_(clock_, timing_.get()),
207 rtp_video_stream_receiver_(clock_,
208 &transport_adapter_,
209 call_stats,
210 packet_router,
211 &config_,
212 rtp_receive_statistics_.get(),
213 &stats_proxy_,
214 &stats_proxy_,
215 process_thread_,
216 this, // NackSender
217 nullptr, // Use default KeyFrameRequestSender
218 this, // OnCompleteFrameCallback
219 config_.frame_decryptor,
220 config_.frame_transformer),
221 rtp_stream_sync_(this),
222 max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_(kMaxWaitForKeyFrameMs),
223 max_wait_for_frame_ms_(kMaxWaitForFrameMs),
224 decode_queue_(task_queue_factory_->CreateTaskQueue(
225 "DecodingQueue",
226 TaskQueueFactory::Priority::HIGH)) {
227 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "VideoReceiveStream: " << config_.ToString();
228
229 RTC_DCHECK(config_.renderer);
230 RTC_DCHECK(process_thread_);
231 RTC_DCHECK(call_stats_);
232
233 module_process_sequence_checker_.Detach();
234 network_sequence_checker_.Detach();
235
236 RTC_DCHECK(!config_.decoders.empty());
237 RTC_CHECK(config_.decoder_factory);
238 std::set<int> decoder_payload_types;
239 for (const Decoder& decoder : config_.decoders) {
240 RTC_CHECK(decoder_payload_types.find(decoder.payload_type) ==
241 decoder_payload_types.end())
242 << "Duplicate payload type (" << decoder.payload_type
243 << ") for different decoders.";
244 decoder_payload_types.insert(decoder.payload_type);
245 }
246
247 timing_->set_render_delay(config_.render_delay_ms);
248
249 frame_buffer_.reset(
250 new video_coding::FrameBuffer(clock_, timing_.get(), &stats_proxy_));
251
252 process_thread_->RegisterModule(&rtp_stream_sync_, RTC_FROM_HERE);
253 // Register with RtpStreamReceiverController.
254 media_receiver_ = receiver_controller->CreateReceiver(
255 config_.rtp.remote_ssrc, &rtp_video_stream_receiver_);
256 if (config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc) {
257 rtx_receive_stream_ = std::make_unique<RtxReceiveStream>(
258 &rtp_video_stream_receiver_, config.rtp.rtx_associated_payload_types,
259 config_.rtp.remote_ssrc, rtp_receive_statistics_.get());
260 rtx_receiver_ = receiver_controller->CreateReceiver(
261 config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc, rtx_receive_stream_.get());
262 } else {
263 rtp_receive_statistics_->EnableRetransmitDetection(config.rtp.remote_ssrc,
264 true);
265 }
266}

308void VideoReceiveStream::Start() {
309 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
310
311 if (decoder_running_) {
312 return;
313 }
314
315 const bool protected_by_fec = config_.rtp.protected_by_flexfec ||
316 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.IsUlpfecEnabled();
317
318 if (rtp_video_stream_receiver_.IsRetransmissionsEnabled() &&
319 protected_by_fec) {
320 frame_buffer_->SetProtectionMode(kProtectionNackFEC);
321 }
322
323 transport_adapter_.Enable();
324 rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>* renderer = nullptr;
325 if (config_.enable_prerenderer_smoothing) {
326 incoming_video_stream_.reset(new IncomingVideoStream(
327 task_queue_factory_, config_.render_delay_ms, this));
328 renderer = incoming_video_stream_.get();
329 } else {
330 renderer = this;
331 }
332
333 for (const Decoder& decoder : config_.decoders) {
334 std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoder> video_decoder =
335 config_.decoder_factory->CreateVideoDecoder(decoder.video_format);
336 // If we still have no valid decoder, we have to create a "Null" decoder
337 // that ignores all calls. The reason we can get into this state is that the
338 // old decoder factory interface doesn't have a way to query supported
339 // codecs.
340 if (!video_decoder) {
341 video_decoder = std::make_unique<NullVideoDecoder>();
342 }
343
344 std::string decoded_output_file =
345 field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-DecoderDataDumpDirectory");
346 // Because '/' can't be used inside a field trial parameter, we use ';'
347 // instead.
348 // This is only relevant to WebRTC-DecoderDataDumpDirectory
349 // field trial. ';' is chosen arbitrary. Even though it's a legal character
350 // in some file systems, we can sacrifice ability to use it in the path to
351 // dumped video, since it's developers-only feature for debugging.
352 absl::c_replace(decoded_output_file, ';', '/');
353 if (!decoded_output_file.empty()) {
354 char filename_buffer[256];
355 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder ssb(filename_buffer);
356 ssb << decoded_output_file << "/webrtc_receive_stream_"
357 << this->config_.rtp.remote_ssrc << "-" << rtc::TimeMicros()
358 << ".ivf";
359 video_decoder = CreateFrameDumpingDecoderWrapper(
360 std::move(video_decoder), FileWrapper::OpenWriteOnly(ssb.str()));
361 }
362
363 video_decoders_.push_back(std::move(video_decoder));
364
365 video_receiver_.RegisterExternalDecoder(video_decoders_.back().get(),
366 decoder.payload_type);
367 VideoCodec codec = CreateDecoderVideoCodec(decoder);
368
369 const bool raw_payload =
370 config_.rtp.raw_payload_types.count(decoder.payload_type) > 0;
371 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.AddReceiveCodec(decoder.payload_type, codec,
372 decoder.video_format.parameters,
373 raw_payload);
374 RTC_CHECK_EQ(VCM_OK, video_receiver_.RegisterReceiveCodec(
375 decoder.payload_type, &codec, num_cpu_cores_));
376 }
377
378 RTC_DCHECK(renderer != nullptr);
379 video_stream_decoder_.reset(
380 new VideoStreamDecoder(&video_receiver_, &stats_proxy_, renderer));
381
382 // Make sure we register as a stats observer *after* we've prepared the
383 // |video_stream_decoder_|.
384 call_stats_->RegisterStatsObserver(this);
385
386 // Start decoding on task queue.
387 video_receiver_.DecoderThreadStarting();
388 stats_proxy_.DecoderThreadStarting();
389 decode_queue_.PostTask([this] {
390 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
391 decoder_stopped_ = false;
392 StartNextDecode();
393 });
394 decoder_running_ = true;
395 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.StartReceive();
396}
397
398void VideoReceiveStream::Stop() {
399 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
400 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.StopReceive();
401
402 stats_proxy_.OnUniqueFramesCounted(
403 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.GetUniqueFramesSeen());
404
405 decode_queue_.PostTask([this] { frame_buffer_->Stop(); });
406
407 call_stats_->DeregisterStatsObserver(this);
408
409 if (decoder_running_) {
410 rtc::Event done;
411 decode_queue_.PostTask([this, &done] {
412 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
413 decoder_stopped_ = true;
414 done.Set();
415 });
416 done.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
417
418 decoder_running_ = false;
419 video_receiver_.DecoderThreadStopped();
420 stats_proxy_.DecoderThreadStopped();
421 // Deregister external decoders so they are no longer running during
422 // destruction. This effectively stops the VCM since the decoder thread is
423 // stopped, the VCM is deregistered and no asynchronous decoder threads are
424 // running.
425 for (const Decoder& decoder : config_.decoders)
426 video_receiver_.RegisterExternalDecoder(nullptr, decoder.payload_type);
427
428 UpdateHistograms();
429 }
430
431 video_stream_decoder_.reset();
432 incoming_video_stream_.reset();
433 transport_adapter_.Disable();
434}

436VideoReceiveStream::Stats VideoReceiveStream::GetStats() const {
437 VideoReceiveStream::Stats stats = stats_proxy_.GetStats();
438 stats.total_bitrate_bps = 0;
439 StreamStatistician* statistician =
440 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(stats.ssrc);
441 if (statistician) {
442 stats.rtp_stats = statistician->GetStats();
443 stats.total_bitrate_bps = statistician->BitrateReceived();
444 }
445 if (config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc) {
446 StreamStatistician* rtx_statistician =
447 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc);
448 if (rtx_statistician)
449 stats.total_bitrate_bps += rtx_statistician->BitrateReceived();
450 }
451 return stats;
452}
453
454void VideoReceiveStream::UpdateHistograms() {
455 absl::optional<int> fraction_lost;
456 StreamDataCounters rtp_stats;
457 StreamStatistician* statistician =
458 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(config_.rtp.remote_ssrc);
459 if (statistician) {
460 fraction_lost = statistician->GetFractionLostInPercent();
461 rtp_stats = statistician->GetReceiveStreamDataCounters();
462 }
463 if (config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc) {
464 StreamStatistician* rtx_statistician =
465 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc);
466 if (rtx_statistician) {
467 StreamDataCounters rtx_stats =
468 rtx_statistician->GetReceiveStreamDataCounters();
469 stats_proxy_.UpdateHistograms(fraction_lost, rtp_stats, &rtx_stats);
470 return;
471 }
472 }
473 stats_proxy_.UpdateHistograms(fraction_lost, rtp_stats, nullptr);
474}

485bool VideoReceiveStream::SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(int delay_ms) {
486 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
487 if (delay_ms < kMinBaseMinimumDelayMs || delay_ms > kMaxBaseMinimumDelayMs) {
488 return false;
489 }
490
491 MutexLock lock(&playout_delay_lock_);
492 base_minimum_playout_delay_ms_ = delay_ms;
493 UpdatePlayoutDelays();
494 return true;
495}
496
497int VideoReceiveStream::GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs() const {
498 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
499
500 MutexLock lock(&playout_delay_lock_);
501 return base_minimum_playout_delay_ms_;
502}

504// TODO(tommi): This method grabs a lock 6 times.
505void VideoReceiveStream::OnFrame(const VideoFrame& video_frame) {
506 int64_t video_playout_ntp_ms;
507 int64_t sync_offset_ms;
508 double estimated_freq_khz;
509 // TODO(tommi): GetStreamSyncOffsetInMs grabs three locks. One inside the
510 // function itself, another in GetChannel() and a third in
511 // GetPlayoutTimestamp. Seems excessive. Anyhow, I'm assuming the function
512 // succeeds most of the time, which leads to grabbing a fourth lock.
513 if (rtp_stream_sync_.GetStreamSyncOffsetInMs(
514 video_frame.timestamp(), video_frame.render_time_ms(),
515 &video_playout_ntp_ms, &sync_offset_ms, &estimated_freq_khz)) {
516 // TODO(tommi): OnSyncOffsetUpdated grabs a lock.
517 stats_proxy_.OnSyncOffsetUpdated(video_playout_ntp_ms, sync_offset_ms,
518 estimated_freq_khz);
519 }
520 source_tracker_.OnFrameDelivered(video_frame.packet_infos());
521
522 config_.renderer->OnFrame(video_frame);
523
524 // TODO(tommi): OnRenderFrame grabs a lock too.
525 stats_proxy_.OnRenderedFrame(video_frame);
526}

550void VideoReceiveStream::OnCompleteFrame(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) {
551 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&network_sequence_checker_);
552 // TODO(https://bugs.webrtc.org/9974): Consider removing this workaround.
553 int64_t time_now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
554 if (last_complete_frame_time_ms_ > 0 &&
555 time_now_ms - last_complete_frame_time_ms_ > kInactiveStreamThresholdMs) {
556 frame_buffer_->Clear();
557 }
558 last_complete_frame_time_ms_ = time_now_ms;
559
560 const VideoPlayoutDelay& playout_delay = frame->EncodedImage().playout_delay_;
561 if (playout_delay.min_ms >= 0) {
562 MutexLock lock(&playout_delay_lock_);
563 frame_minimum_playout_delay_ms_ = playout_delay.min_ms;
564 UpdatePlayoutDelays();
565 }
566
567 if (playout_delay.max_ms >= 0) {
568 MutexLock lock(&playout_delay_lock_);
569 frame_maximum_playout_delay_ms_ = playout_delay.max_ms;
570 UpdatePlayoutDelays();
571 }
572
573 int64_t last_continuous_pid = frame_buffer_->InsertFrame(std::move(frame));
574 if (last_continuous_pid != -1)
575 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.FrameContinuous(last_continuous_pid);
576}

621int64_t VideoReceiveStream::GetWaitMs() const {
622 return keyframe_required_ ? max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_
623 : max_wait_for_frame_ms_;
624}
625
626void VideoReceiveStream::StartNextDecode() {
627 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VideoReceiveStream::StartNextDecode");
628 frame_buffer_->NextFrame(
629 GetWaitMs(), keyframe_required_, &decode_queue_,
630 /* encoded frame handler */
631 [this](std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame, ReturnReason res) {
632 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame == nullptr, res == ReturnReason::kTimeout);
633 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame != nullptr, res == ReturnReason::kFrameFound);
634 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
635 if (decoder_stopped_)
636 return;
637 if (frame) {
638 HandleEncodedFrame(std::move(frame));
639 } else {
640 HandleFrameBufferTimeout();
641 }
642 StartNextDecode();
643 });
644}
645
646void VideoReceiveStream::HandleEncodedFrame(
647 std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) {
648 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
649
650 // Current OnPreDecode only cares about QP for VP8.
651 int qp = -1;
652 if (frame->CodecSpecific()->codecType == kVideoCodecVP8) {
653 if (!vp8::GetQp(frame->data(), frame->size(), &qp)) {
654 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to extract QP from VP8 video frame";
655 }
656 }
657 stats_proxy_.OnPreDecode(frame->CodecSpecific()->codecType, qp);
658 HandleKeyFrameGeneration(frame->FrameType() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey,
659 now_ms);
660 int decode_result = video_receiver_.Decode(frame.get());
661 if (decode_result == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK ||
662 decode_result == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK_REQUEST_KEYFRAME) {
663 keyframe_required_ = false;
664 frame_decoded_ = true;
665 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.FrameDecoded(frame->Id());
666
667 if (decode_result == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK_REQUEST_KEYFRAME)
668 RequestKeyFrame(now_ms);
669 } else if (!frame_decoded_ || !keyframe_required_ ||
670 (last_keyframe_request_ms_ + max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_ < now_ms)) {
671 keyframe_required_ = true;
672 // TODO(philipel): Remove this keyframe request when downstream project
673 // has been fixed.
674 RequestKeyFrame(now_ms);
675 }
676
677 if (encoded_frame_buffer_function_) {
678 encoded_frame_buffer_function_(WebRtcRecordableEncodedFrame(*frame));
679 }
680}
681
682void VideoReceiveStream::HandleKeyFrameGeneration(
683 bool received_frame_is_keyframe,
684 int64_t now_ms) {
685 // Repeat sending keyframe requests if we've requested a keyframe.
686 if (!keyframe_generation_requested_) {
687 return;
688 }
689 if (received_frame_is_keyframe) {
690 keyframe_generation_requested_ = false;
691 } else if (last_keyframe_request_ms_ + max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_ <= now_ms) {
692 if (!IsReceivingKeyFrame(now_ms)) {
693 RequestKeyFrame(now_ms);
694 }
695 } else {
696 // It hasn't been long enough since the last keyframe request, do nothing.
697 }
698}
699
700void VideoReceiveStream::HandleFrameBufferTimeout() {
701 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
702 absl::optional<int64_t> last_packet_ms =
703 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.LastReceivedPacketMs();
704
705 // To avoid spamming keyframe requests for a stream that is not active we
706 // check if we have received a packet within the last 5 seconds.
707 bool stream_is_active = last_packet_ms && now_ms - *last_packet_ms < 5000;
708 if (!stream_is_active)
709 stats_proxy_.OnStreamInactive();
710
711 if (stream_is_active && !IsReceivingKeyFrame(now_ms) &&
712 (!config_.crypto_options.sframe.require_frame_encryption ||
713 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.IsDecryptable())) {
714 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "No decodable frame in " << GetWaitMs()
715 << " ms, requesting keyframe.";
716 RequestKeyFrame(now_ms);
717 }
718}
719
720bool VideoReceiveStream::IsReceivingKeyFrame(int64_t timestamp_ms) const {
721 absl::optional<int64_t> last_keyframe_packet_ms =
722 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.LastReceivedKeyframePacketMs();
723
724 // If we recently have been receiving packets belonging to a keyframe then
725 // we assume a keyframe is currently being received.
726 bool receiving_keyframe =
727 last_keyframe_packet_ms &&
728 timestamp_ms - *last_keyframe_packet_ms < max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_;
729 return receiving_keyframe;
730}
731
732void VideoReceiveStream::UpdatePlayoutDelays() const {
733 const int minimum_delay_ms =
734 std::max({frame_minimum_playout_delay_ms_, base_minimum_playout_delay_ms_,
735 syncable_minimum_playout_delay_ms_});
736 if (minimum_delay_ms >= 0) {
737 timing_->set_min_playout_delay(minimum_delay_ms);
738 }
739
740 const int maximum_delay_ms = frame_maximum_playout_delay_ms_;
741 if (maximum_delay_ms >= 0) {
742 timing_->set_max_playout_delay(maximum_delay_ms);
743 }
744}

746std::vector<webrtc::RtpSource> VideoReceiveStream::GetSources() const {
747 return source_tracker_.GetSources();
748}
749
750VideoReceiveStream::RecordingState VideoReceiveStream::SetAndGetRecordingState(
751 RecordingState state,
752 bool generate_key_frame) {
753 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
754 rtc::Event event;
755 RecordingState old_state;
756 decode_queue_.PostTask([this, &event, &old_state, generate_key_frame,
757 state = std::move(state)] {
758 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
759 // Save old state.
760 old_state.callback = std::move(encoded_frame_buffer_function_);
761 old_state.keyframe_needed = keyframe_generation_requested_;
762 old_state.last_keyframe_request_ms = last_keyframe_request_ms_;
763
764 // Set new state.
765 encoded_frame_buffer_function_ = std::move(state.callback);
766 if (generate_key_frame) {
767 RequestKeyFrame(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
768 keyframe_generation_requested_ = true;
769 } else {
770 keyframe_generation_requested_ = state.keyframe_needed;
771 last_keyframe_request_ms_ = state.last_keyframe_request_ms.value_or(0);
772 }
773 event.Set();
774 });
775 event.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
776 return old_state;
777}
778
779void VideoReceiveStream::GenerateKeyFrame() {
780 decode_queue_.PostTask([this]() {
781 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
782 RequestKeyFrame(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
783 keyframe_generation_requested_ = true;
784 });
785}
